# Component Library — Lookup & Usage Rules

## Where the Library Lives
The component reference library is located at:
```
Mashup Manager/Components Library/
  ids-enterprise-ng/          ← TypeScript type definitions (Angular wrappers)
    lib/<component>/
      soho-<component>.component.d.ts   ← @Inputs, @Outputs, public API
      soho-<component>.module.d.ts
      index.d.ts
  scraped_components/         ← Live HTML examples from the IDS demo site
    <component-slug>/
      example-index_html/page.html      ← Basic usage example
      example-<variant>_html/page.html  ← Variant examples
    _index.json               ← Master list of all components with slugs
```

---

## MANDATORY: Always Consult the Library Before Generating a Component

Before writing any IDS component implementation:

### Step 1 — Find the component slug
Open `Mashup Manager/Components Library/scraped_components/_index.json` and find the matching entry. Use the `"slug"` field to locate the correct folder.

### Step 2 — Read the TypeScript definition
Open `Mashup Manager/Components Library/ids-enterprise-ng/lib/<component-name>/soho-<component>.component.d.ts`.
This file defines:
- All `@Input()` property names and types
- All `@Output()` event emitter names and payload types  
- Public methods you can call via `@ViewChild` reference
- Available option interfaces (e.g. `SohoButtonOptions`, `SohoDataGridOptions`)

### Step 3 — Read the HTML examples
Open `Mashup Manager/Components Library/scraped_components/<slug>/example-index_html/page.html` to see the canonical HTML markup for that component. Use further `example-*_html/page.html` files for variants (grouping, paging, editable, etc.).

### Step 4 — Write the implementation
Use ONLY the documented `@Input`/`@Output` names from the `.d.ts`. Do NOT invent property names.

